    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>pork loin steak[s] </strong>dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rub with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season both sides with your <strong>five-spice mix</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned steak[s] </strong>and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until browned and cooked through</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the pork is cooking, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spring greens </strong>then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rip the leaves off your <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>,<strong> rice vinegar </strong>and <strong>soy sauce</strong> in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Once the pork is cooked, reduce the heat to low and add the <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for a further 1 min, turning the pork steaks several times until they're nicely coated</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat and set aside to rest for a couple of min \u2013 these are your <strong>Taiwanese-style pork steaks</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong>, <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and cook, covered for 3-4 min or until tender \u2013 these are your <strong>sesame greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the veg is cooking, trim, then slice your<strong> spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Roughly chop the <strong>peanuts </strong>(or bash them in their bag!)</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-style-pork-with-sesame-greens-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>rested Taiwanese-style pork steaks </strong>over the<strong> cooked rice </strong>with the <strong>sesame greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle over any<strong> remaining hoisin sauce</strong> from the pan and garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong> and <strong>chopped peanuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
